<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,579,605]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[561,654,580,606]" name="Senegal" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Senegal</collectingCountry>
is teneral and was wrongly assumed to be an unusual variant of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lauxaniidae" genus="Dacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apoxanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">D. apoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="White" box="[332,495,618,644]" pageId="27" pageNumber="49" refString="White, I. M. (2006) Taxonomy of the Dacina (Diptera: Tephritidae) of Africa and the Middle East. African Entomology, Memoir, 2, 1 - 156." type="journal article" year="2006">
White (
<number box="[421,486,618,644]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[756,844,618,644]" name="Nigeria" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
are mature and the differences from southern and eastern African 
<taxonomicName box="[338,509,657,682]" class="Insecta" family="Lauxaniidae" genus="Dacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apoxanthus">
<emphasis box="[338,509,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">D. apoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both distinct and consistent.
</paragraph>
